%define name @PACKAGE@
%define version @VERSION@
%define release mandriva
%define _topdir %(echo $PWD)/rpm

Name: %{name}
Version: %{version}
Release: %{release}
License: GPL
Group: Application/Misc
URL: http://groups.google.com/group/gebr
Packager: Bráulio Barros de Oliveira <brauliobo@gmail.com>
Source: %{name}-%{version}.tar.gz
Requires: libglib2.0_0 >= 2.8.0, libgdome0
BuildRoot: /tmp/%{name}-%{version}
Summary: GêBR library collecion
%description
GêBR is an environment to seismic processing based on open-source
technologies, designed to easily assembly and run processing flows.

What GêBR does:

    * Handle projects and lines
    * Assembly and run processing flows
    * Act as an interface to many freely-available seismic-processing
      packages (Seismic Unix, Madagascar, etc)

libgebr is the collection of libraries of GêBR:
    * libgebr_geoxml is the XML engine of GêBR
    * libgebr_misc network and process classes.

%prep
%setup -q

%configure

%build
make -j 4

%install
rm -rf %{buildroot}
mkdir -p %{buildroot}

%makeinstall

%clean
rm -rf %{buildroot}

%files
%defattr(-,root,root)
%{_bindir}/*
%{_libdir}/*
%{_includedir}/%{name}/*
%{_datadir}/%{name}/*
%{_mandir}/*
%{_infodir}/*

%changelog
